    <h2>(language)</h2>
    <p><b>HTML</b> - Hyper Text Markup Language<br>
    â†’ for writing content to websites.</p>

    <h2>(opening a website)</h2>
    <p>All elements go in <span class="code">&lt;element&gt;</span> format.</p>

    <h2>(common elements)</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><span class="code">&lt;p&gt;</span> - paragraph element.</li>
        <li><span class="code">&lt;b&gt;</span> - bold</li>
        <li><span class="code">&lt;li&gt;</span> - ordered list</li>
        <li><span class="code">&lt;ul&gt;</span> - unordered list</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="divider"></div>

    <h2>(family tree structure)</h2>
    <p>HTML is structured like so:</p>
    <pre class="code">
&lt;html&gt;
  &lt;body&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
    </pre>
    <p>So open, open, open, close, close, close.<br>Parents and children.</p>

    <div class="divider"></div>

